    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "\n<p class=\"has-text-align-right has-small-font-size\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/blocks/\">Go back to the list of <strong>Blocks</strong></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Pagination</strong><em> </em>block<em> </em>displays paginated navigation to the next/previous set of posts, when applicable. This block is located inside a <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/query-loop-block/\" data-type=\"helphub_article\" data-id=\"14633622\">Query Loop</a> block and lets you customize the layout and appearance of the navigation.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"3294\" height=\"1458\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.26.15\u202fPM.png\" alt=\"Pagination Block\" class=\"wp-image-16359836\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.26.15\u202fPM.png 3294w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.26.15\u202fPM-300x133.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.26.15\u202fPM-1024x453.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.26.15\u202fPM-768x340.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.26.15\u202fPM-1536x680.png 1536w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.26.15\u202fPM-2048x906.png 2048w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 3294px) 100vw, 3294px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>A <strong>Pagination</strong> block is included by default if you choose a correct pattern in a Query Loop block. That said, you can also insert it manually when needed.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Click the <strong>add block</strong> (<strong>+</strong>) icon inside the Query Loop block to open the <strong>block inserter</strong> pop-up window and search for the <strong>Pagination</strong> block.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also use the keyboard shortcut <kbd>/pagination</kbd> in a new paragraph block followed by&nbsp;<code>enter</code> to insert a block quickly.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"722\" height=\"482\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.24.49\u202fPM.png\" alt=\"How to quickly add a pagination block via shortcut\" class=\"wp-image-16359835\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.24.49\u202fPM.png 722w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.24.49\u202fPM-300x200.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 722px) 100vw, 722px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\">Detailed instructions on adding blocks can be found <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/adding-a-new-block/\" data-type=\"helphub_article\" data-id=\"11656696\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Block toolbar</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"840\" height=\"240\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.23.28\u202fPM-1.png\" alt=\"Block Toolbar in the Pagination Block\" class=\"wp-image-16359837\" style=\"width:457px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.23.28\u202fPM-1.png 840w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.23.28\u202fPM-1-300x86.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.23.28\u202fPM-1-768x219.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The block toolbar contains the tools to customize each block. The <strong>Pagination</strong> block\u2019s toolbar consists of the following tools:</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Transform to</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"784\" height=\"430\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.28.44\u202fPM.png\" alt=\"Transform To in a Pagination block\" class=\"wp-image-16359838\" style=\"width:388px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.28.44\u202fPM.png 784w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.28.44\u202fPM-300x165.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.28.44\u202fPM-768x421.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 784px) 100vw, 784px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can transform a <strong>Pagination</strong> block into a Columns, or a Group block.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Block-moving tools</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"748\" height=\"156\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.29.43\u202fPM.png\" alt=\"Block moving tools in the Pagination block\" class=\"wp-image-16359839\" style=\"width:507px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.29.43\u202fPM.png 748w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.29.43\u202fPM-300x63.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 748px) 100vw, 748px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Use the block-moving tools to move the block up and down inside the editor. Use the six dots icon to drag and drop the <strong>Pagination</strong> block and reposition it anywhere on the editor. Alternatively, click on the up and down arrows to move the block up or down the editor.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Change items justification</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"796\" height=\"508\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.30.39\u202fPM.png\" alt=\"Change Items Justification in the Pagination block\" class=\"wp-image-16359840\" style=\"width:460px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.30.39\u202fPM.png 796w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.30.39\u202fPM-300x191.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.30.39\u202fPM-768x490.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 796px) 100vw, 796px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Change items justification</strong> tool lets you change the horizontal placement of the items inside the <strong>Pagination</strong> block. There are four options to choose from:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Justify items left</strong> will move the items toward the left side of the block.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Justify items center </strong>will move the items toward the center of the block.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Justify items right</strong> will move the items toward the right side of the block.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Space between items </strong>will distribute all items across the block and automatically adjust the space between them.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Change vertical alignment</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"796\" height=\"508\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.31.12\u202fPM.png\" alt=\"Change Vertical Alignment in the Pagination block\" class=\"wp-image-16359841\" style=\"width:503px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.31.12\u202fPM.png 796w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.31.12\u202fPM-300x191.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.31.12\u202fPM-768x490.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 796px) 100vw, 796px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Change vertical alignment </strong>tool lets you choose the vertical position of the items inside the <strong>Pagination</strong> block. You can choose between top, middle, and bottom vertical alignment.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Change alignment</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"980\" height=\"490\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.32.35\u202fPM.png\" alt=\"Change Alignment in the Pagination block\" class=\"wp-image-16359842\" style=\"width:523px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.32.35\u202fPM.png 980w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.32.35\u202fPM-300x150.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.32.35\u202fPM-768x384.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 980px) 100vw, 980px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Unlike the previous alignment tools, the <strong>Change alignment</strong> tool is used for the <strong>Pagination</strong> block\u2019s position inside the Query Loop block. Choose one of the following block alignment options:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>None</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Wide width&nbsp;</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Full width</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Align left</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Align center</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Align right</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">More options</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"965\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.33.23\u202fPM-1024x965.png\" alt=\"More Options in the Pagination block\" class=\"wp-image-16359843\" style=\"width:463px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.33.23\u202fPM-1024x965.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.33.23\u202fPM-300x283.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.33.23\u202fPM-768x724.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.33.23\u202fPM.png 1182w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on the three dots icon to show more block options. A drop-down menu with these actions will appear:</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Details about <strong>More options</strong> can be found in this <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/more-options/\" data-type=\"helphub_article\" data-id=\"13748329\">support article</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Block settings</h2>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Layout</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Pagination </strong>block<em> </em>provides Layout settings options to change the justification or orientation of the text and to wrap to multiple lines.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For details, refer to this support article: <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/layout-settings-overview/\">Layout settings overview</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Settings</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>settings</strong> tab lets you change the decorative arrow appended to the next and previous page links. You can choose between <strong>None</strong>, <strong>Arrow, </strong>and<strong> Chevron</strong> icons. You can also choose whether to display or hide the label text based on what you prefer.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"473\" height=\"393\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image.png\" alt=\"Pagination block settings with the option to show or hide label text\" class=\"wp-image-16358914\" style=\"width:426px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image.png 473w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/10/image-300x249.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 473px) 100vw, 473px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Color</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong><strong><strong>Pagination</strong></strong></strong> block provides color settings options to change the text, background, and link colors. It can be found in the Styles tab.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"545\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.35.45\u202fPM-545x1024.png\" alt=\"Color options in the Pagination block\" class=\"wp-image-16359844\" style=\"width:323px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.35.45\u202fPM-545x1024.png 545w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.35.45\u202fPM-160x300.png 160w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.35.45\u202fPM.png 572w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 545px) 100vw, 545px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For details refer to this support article: <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/colors-settings-overview/\">Color settings overview</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Typography</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong><strong>Pagination </strong></strong>block provides typography settings to change the font family, appearance, line height, letter spacing, decoration, letter case, and font size. This can be found in the Styles tab.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For details refer to this support article: <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/typography-settings-overview/\">Typography settings overview</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Advanced</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Advanced tab lets you add CSS class(es) to your block. This will allow you to write custom CSS and styles for the block.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/11/Screenshot-2022-11-11-at-11.26.17-AM-1.png\" alt=\"Advanced tab with additional CSS\" class=\"wp-image-16190554\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Advanced option in the Pagination Block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-video\"><video controls src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/pagination-block-styles-tab.mp4\"></video></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Typography settings (<em>Font, Size, Appearance, Line Height, Letter Spacing, Decoration, and Letter Case</em>) have been moved to the <strong>Styles</strong> tab.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Pagination inner blocks </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Pagination</strong> block consists of the following three inner blocks (which can\u2019t be inserted on their own):</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Previous Page block</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Page Numbers block</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Next Page block</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Previous Page</strong><em> </em>block<em> </em>displays the previous posts page link. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Page Numbers </strong>block<em> </em>displays a list of page numbers for pagination. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Next Page </strong>block<em> </em>displays the next posts page link.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>All these blocks are located inside a Query Loop block and lets you customize the appearance of the Pagination for the query loop.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"726\" height=\"228\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.43.35\u202fPM.png\" alt=\"Previous Page in the Pagination Block\" class=\"wp-image-16359845\" style=\"width:344px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.43.35\u202fPM.png 726w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.43.35\u202fPM-300x94.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 726px) 100vw, 726px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Previous Page</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"726\" height=\"228\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.43.44\u202fPM.png\" alt=\"Page Numbers in the Pagination Block\" class=\"wp-image-16359846\" style=\"width:430px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.43.44\u202fPM.png 726w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.43.44\u202fPM-300x94.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 726px) 100vw, 726px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Page Numbers</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"726\" height=\"228\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.43.51\u202fPM.png\" alt=\"Next Page in the Pagination block\" class=\"wp-image-16359847\" style=\"width:522px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.43.51\u202fPM.png 726w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.43.51\u202fPM-300x94.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 726px) 100vw, 726px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Next Page</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Block toolbar</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The block toolbar for all the <strong>Pagination </strong>inner blocks &#8211;<strong>Previous Page</strong>, <strong>Page Numbers</strong> and <strong>Next Page</strong> contains the tools to customize each block. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Block-moving tools</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"726\" height=\"228\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.47.30\u202fPM.png\" alt=\"Block Moving Tool in the Pagination Block\" class=\"wp-image-16359848\" style=\"width:520px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.47.30\u202fPM.png 726w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.47.30\u202fPM-300x94.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 726px) 100vw, 726px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Use the block-moving tools to move the block up and down inside the editor. Use the six dots icon to drag and drop the block and reposition it anywhere on the editor. Alternatively, click on the up and down arrows to move the block up or down the editor.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">More options</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Page Numbers, Next Page and Previous page blocks share the same functionality for more block options button. Click on the three dots icon to show <strong>More block</strong> options. A drop-down menu with these actions will appear:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"960\" height=\"886\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.48.16\u202fPM-1.png\" alt=\"More Options in the Pagination Block\" class=\"wp-image-16359850\" style=\"width:368px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.48.16\u202fPM-1.png 960w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.48.16\u202fPM-1-300x277.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.48.16\u202fPM-1-768x709.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Block settings</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The block settings panel contains customization options specific to the block. To open it, select the block and click the cog icon in the sidebar.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"451\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.50.12\u202fPM-451x1024.png\" alt=\"Cog Options in the Pagination Block\" class=\"wp-image-16359851\" style=\"width:260px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.50.12\u202fPM-451x1024.png 451w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.50.12\u202fPM-132x300.png 132w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/Screenshot-2024-03-07-at-3.50.12\u202fPM.png 564w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 451px) 100vw, 451px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are the options for the <strong>Pagination</strong> inner blocks:</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Color</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Pagination </strong>inner blocks &#8211;<strong>Previous Page</strong>, <strong>Page Numbers</strong> and <strong>Next Page</strong>&#8211;<strong> </strong>provides color settings option to add background color.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For details refer to this support article: <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/colors-settings-overview/\">Color settings overview</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Typography</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Pagination </strong>inner blocks (<strong>Previous Page</strong>, <strong>Page Numbers</strong> and <strong>Next Page</strong>) provides typography settings to change the font family, appearance, line height, letter spacing, decoration, letter case, and font size.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Typography settings (<em>Font, Size, Appearance, Line Height, Letter Spacing, Decoration, and Letter Case</em>) specific to the <strong>Page Numbers</strong> inner block have been moved to the <strong>Styles</strong> tab.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For details refer to this support article: <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/typography-settings-overview/\">Typography settings overview</a></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-video\"><video controls src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/page-numbers-block-styles-tab.mp4\"></video></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Advanced</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Advanced</strong> tab lets you add CSS class(es) to your block. This will allow you to write custom CSS and styles for the block.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/11/Screenshot-2022-11-11-at-11.26.17-AM-1.png\" alt=\"Advanced tab with additional CSS\" class=\"wp-image-16190554\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Advanced option in the selected Block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<div id=\"changelog\" class=\"wp-block-group changelog has-background is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow\" style=\"background-color:#dce5ec\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Changelog</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated 2023-03-07\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated the videos to show the Styles tab where the Typography settings now resides</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated the screenshots</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2023-10-04\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated for 6.3</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Created 2022-12-12</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n",
